@node "intro" "WhadIzDiz?"

This is a small utility that will list the attributes of an Imagine (TDDD)
attribute or object file. It will also list the attributes of object groups
stating each object's name. Attributes include color, reflect etc. and texture
and brush settings. Not included are the texture's parameter settings as the
parameter names are included in the textures themselves. I don't know if it
would be possible to list the parameters. Also not included are lists of
particle settings, states and subgroups. If anybody needs this info, please
let me know, I will see what I can do.

ListAtts intentionally leaves unused attributes out, to make the output more
readable, these attributes include reflection, filter, specular/hardness and
other things, but not phong; phong is shown whether it's on or off, because it
is easily taken for granted (because it is usually on).
@endnode

@node "install" "Installazione"

Just copy it to the c: directory or any place you would like it to be.
@endnode

@node "Usage" "Uzeme"

@{fg fill}(from shell) ListAtts <Imagine 3.x/4.x tdddfile>@{fg text}

The output of ListAtts can be quite extensive, especially when multiple
brushes, textures and/or objects are used. If you are not using KingCon (an
excellent utillity, get it now) the information will scroll out of the window,
never to return again (how dramatic). Luckily AmigaDOS lets you redirect the
output to a file, for instance:

@{fg fill}ListAtts >work:ballatts.list ball.obj@{fg text}

This will list the attributes of the object 'ball.obj' to a file called
ballatts.list (what a name) on the work: partition. You can now view it using
'more' or your favourite text editor.
@endnode

